==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Mallard
<hw>Mal"lard</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>malari</ets>,fr. <ets>m⟦acir⟧le</ets> male + <ets>-art</ets> =
<ets>-ard</ets>. See <er>Male</er>, <pos>a.</pos>, and
<er>-ard</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A drake; the
male of <spn>Anas boschas</spn>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A large wild duck (<spn>Anas
boschas</spn>) inhabiting both America and Europe. The domestic duck has
descended from this species. Called also
<altname>greenhead</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Malleability</ent>⟦br⟧
